{
  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, both pre and post treatment could be crucial to increasing the revenue from BSFL frass as it may give significant impact to the maturity and stability of BSFL frass.",
    "The feed substrate has a large effect on the nutrients in the frass (Elissen et al., 2023).",
    "The nutrient availability of BSFFF is not optimum for plant growth, not for extended root growth which limits the potential of roots to explore nutrients from deeper soil layers (Gebremikael et al., 2022).",
    "The neutral to alkaline pH of the frass can lead to NH 3 emissions in case of higher NH 4 content, but high dry matter contents (Palma et al. (2020) and cannot be applied at high concentrations (Gärttling et al., 2020).",
    "Depending on the geographical region, there may be obstacles in terms of regulations and the absence of established standards for utilizing insect-derived frass as a fertilizer (Poveda, 2021)."
  ]
}